{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Project Overview</h1>\n<p>For the announcement of <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/finance/fiscal-year-2020\">yearly budget</a>, we wanted to integrated the information and numbers about the City's budget into boston.gov </p>\n<p>Each year, the <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/departments/budget\">budget department</a> write the <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/sites/default/files/embed/file/2019-09/1a-volume_1_-_executive_summary.pdf\">Budget Book</a>. Before FY2020, our team's role was to take the Budget Book and use its text to automatically build a 1600 page static site. The site was hard to navigate and separate from boston.gov so couldn't leverage the linking and search indexing we have on our main domain. </p>\n<p>I worked with the Budget Department bring down the reading level their content - inline with our <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/departments/digital-team/city-boston-writing-guide\">site writing guidlines</a>, reduce the number of created pages for the Budget website from 1600 to 27, and build out <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/departments/budget/fy20-operating-budget#revenue\">interactive charting component</a> for use throughout boston.gov. </p>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"imageBlock\">\n    <div>\n        <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/news/building-better-maps-bostongov\">\n            <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 900px;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.93741307371349%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Building better maps for boston.gov\" title src=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/48396/maps-blog-post.png\" srcset=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/39d7a/maps-blog-post.png 225w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/d45f3/maps-blog-post.png 450w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/48396/maps-blog-post.png 900w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/14262/maps-blog-post.png 1350w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/c1e46/maps-blog-post.png 1800w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/83e3a/maps-blog-post.png 2700w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/4bafc/maps-blog-post.png 2876w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\">\n  </span>\n        </a>\n    </div>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Charts on boston.gov","myRole":"Developer and Product Manager"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/charts-boston-gov/"}}